WEBVTT

00:00:00.530 --> 00:00:06.210
In the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, Amen.

00:00:06.210 --> 00:00:13.250
The reading from the Sinaxadion for April 23rd, on which we commemorate, the Holy and

00:00:13.250 --> 00:00:18.980
Glorious Great Marjorie, George the Trophy Bearer.

00:00:18.980 --> 00:00:24.300
On the 23rd of the month, we celebrate the memory of the Holy and Glorious Great Marjorie

00:00:24.300 --> 00:00:34.980
for George the Victory Bearer, and of his companions Anatolios, Protoleon, Athanasios, Anglicarius.

00:00:34.980 --> 00:00:39.860
This great and wonderful athlete of Christ was the son of a wealthy and high-ranking

00:00:39.860 --> 00:00:41.940
Capodoshian family.

00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:48.180
George, having lost his father at the age of ten, his mother, Polychronia, who had become

00:00:48.180 --> 00:00:54.060
a Christian without her husband's knowledge, returned to Palestine, her homeland, and brought

00:00:54.060 --> 00:00:57.860
up her son in the Evangelical virtues.

00:00:57.860 --> 00:01:03.940
Handsome, intelligent, and refined in manner, George embarked on a military career at the

00:01:03.940 --> 00:01:06.020
age of eighteen.

00:01:06.020 --> 00:01:11.980
He pleased his superiors and was quickly promoted to the rank of Tribune in the Imperial Guard,

00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:16.820
and then it would appear to that of Prefect.

00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:21.860
Returning to Capodosia after a victorious campaign and passing through the region of Atalia in

00:01:21.860 --> 00:01:27.300
Pamphilia, he freed the King's daughter, who had been left at the mercy of a dangerous

00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:34.180
dragon, and killed the beast, with the divine strength that he was given by his faith.

00:01:34.180 --> 00:01:38.980
Marveling at this demonstration of the strength given by Christ to his faithful ones, against

00:01:38.980 --> 00:01:44.700
the forces of evil, the local pagans were all converted to Christianity.

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:51.060
At the time of the Great Persecution unleashed by Diocletian, circa the year 304, when the

00:01:51.060 --> 00:01:55.980
Emperor had summoned all the Eastern Governors to Nicomedia to make them privy to his

00:01:55.980 --> 00:01:58.660
decrees against the Christians.

00:01:58.660 --> 00:02:04.260
St. George, sensing that the moment had come for him to make public confession of Christ,

00:02:04.260 --> 00:02:10.740
gave all his goods away to the poor, freed his slaves, and went to court.

00:02:10.740 --> 00:02:16.100
He appeared in the midst of the assembly, and reproached the sovereign for unjustly shedding

00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:18.820
the innocent blood of Christians.

00:02:18.820 --> 00:02:26.300
Diocletian in stupification ordered his second-in-command, Magnentius, to interrogate this insolent

00:02:26.300 --> 00:02:29.260
young man about his faith.

00:02:29.260 --> 00:02:34.860
George replied that it was because he believed in Christ, the true God, that he had come without

00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:37.220
fear to reproach them.

00:02:37.220 --> 00:02:43.460
Having recovered from his amazement, the Emperor, fearing a tumult among those present, offered

00:02:43.460 --> 00:02:50.420
to keep honors on the saint, on condition that he sacrificed to the gods of the Empire.

00:02:50.420 --> 00:02:58.540
George replied, Your reign will become corrupt, and will quickly disappear at no gain to you,

00:02:58.540 --> 00:03:03.580
but those who offer a sacrifice of praise to the King of Heaven will reign with him for

00:03:03.580 --> 00:03:04.980
all eternity.

00:03:04.980 --> 00:03:11.940
At the sovereign's orders, the guards beat the saint on the stomach with their lances.

00:03:11.940 --> 00:03:18.380
His blood flowed down, but at the first blows their weapons became twisted, as though

00:03:18.380 --> 00:03:22.180
they were made of some soft material.

00:03:22.180 --> 00:03:27.220
Christ's soldier was then thrown into prison with a heavy stone on his breast.

00:03:27.220 --> 00:03:33.140
The next day he appeared once more before the tyrant and showed the same firmness.

00:03:33.140 --> 00:03:38.860
They therefore tied him to a wheel, suspended over sharp instruments, so that when the wheel

00:03:38.860 --> 00:03:44.380
was turned, the saint's body would gradually be cut to pieces.

00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:49.940
Overcoming the pain with his overflowing love for God, Saint George unceasingly gave thanks

00:03:49.940 --> 00:03:50.940
to God.

00:03:50.940 --> 00:04:00.260
A voice was then heard from heaven, saying, Fear nothing, George, I am with you.

00:04:00.260 --> 00:04:06.100
And a white clad angel, more resplendent than the sun, descended to lose him and heal

00:04:06.100 --> 00:04:08.100
his wounds.

00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:14.820
When he appeared, safe and sound before the emperor, two officers of the guard, Anatolios

00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:20.260
and Protoleon, confessed Christ with loud voices.

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:22.700
They were beheaded at once.

00:04:22.700 --> 00:04:28.860
The Empress Alexandra also declared herself to be a Christian, but Magnentios constrained

00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:31.460
her to withdraw to the palace.

00:04:31.460 --> 00:04:37.700
They then threw the saint into a ditch filled with quicklime, but like the three young men

00:04:37.780 --> 00:04:45.020
in the Babylonian furnace, he emerged unharmed after three days, greeted by the crowd with

00:04:45.020 --> 00:04:49.060
a cry, Great is George's God.

00:04:49.060 --> 00:04:54.980
The emperor still remaining insensible before all these demonstration of Christ's power ordered

00:04:54.980 --> 00:05:00.380
that the martyr be forced to walk in shoes, studded with red-hot nails.

00:05:00.380 --> 00:05:08.860
Run, George, towards the object of your desire, said the saint, invoking the Lord's help.

00:05:08.860 --> 00:05:14.380
And once again he presented himself whole and radiant with grace before the tyrant.

00:05:14.380 --> 00:05:21.100
By the grace of God he also escaped a poison prepared by a sorcerer called Athanasios.

00:05:21.100 --> 00:05:26.340
When the latter and those of his sort were still incredulous and reckoned that George was

00:05:26.340 --> 00:05:35.580
using magical arts, he at their requests raised a dead man, who had been buried for 300 years,

00:05:35.580 --> 00:05:41.780
the man prostrated before the saint, and declaring that he had been rested from hell at George's

00:05:41.780 --> 00:05:44.580
prayers, he confessed Christ.

00:05:44.580 --> 00:05:51.660
The defeated sorcerer then fell at the feet of the servant of God, and in his turn proclaimed

00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:53.620
the true faith.

00:05:53.620 --> 00:06:01.300
One can decent with rage, diocletian ordered that Athanasios and the resurrected man be beheaded

00:06:01.300 --> 00:06:03.500
without delay.

00:06:03.500 --> 00:06:08.380
Not a few of those who had come to believe in Christ as a result of Saint George's miracles

00:06:08.380 --> 00:06:14.380
found the means to visit him in prison in order to be instructed in the truths of the gospel

00:06:14.380 --> 00:06:17.660
or to receive the healing of their ills.

00:06:17.660 --> 00:06:23.140
The saint had compassion on the sufferings of each of them, and even restored to life

00:06:23.140 --> 00:06:31.380
a bull belonging to a peasant called Gliccedios, who was then arrested and beheaded without

00:06:31.380 --> 00:06:33.820
any sort of trial.

00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:40.340
The next day diocletian had George appear in the temple of Apollo before a fairly large

00:06:40.340 --> 00:06:47.620
crowd, pretending that he intended to offer sacrifice, the martyr went into the temple and confronted

00:06:47.660 --> 00:06:51.740
the idol, making the sign of the cross.

00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:58.220
The demons that lived in the idol then confessed in terror that Christ alone is the true God,

00:06:58.220 --> 00:07:05.020
and they escaped with a great hubbub, leaving the inert statues to fall to the ground.

00:07:05.020 --> 00:07:10.940
The priests and the pagans then drove the saint out with loud cries, and took him back to

00:07:10.940 --> 00:07:12.940
the palace.

00:07:12.940 --> 00:07:18.900
Attracted by the tumult, Empress Alexandra came out and forced her way through the crowd,

00:07:18.900 --> 00:07:27.220
crying out, God of George, come to my aid, and she fell at the saint's feet.

00:07:27.220 --> 00:07:32.860
Unable any longer to contain his fury, the tyrant, whose heart was hardened as pharaohs

00:07:32.860 --> 00:07:38.020
had been of old, ordered that they both be beheaded.

00:07:38.020 --> 00:07:45.100
But, some while before the execution, Alexandra peacefully gave her soul into God's hands

00:07:45.100 --> 00:07:47.260
in prison.

00:07:47.260 --> 00:07:52.780
When the day arrived, Saint George went to the place of execution, followed by a large

00:07:52.780 --> 00:07:53.780
crowd.

00:07:53.780 --> 00:07:58.860
He gave thanks to God for his benefits and begging his help for all those who would trustingly

00:07:58.860 --> 00:08:05.420
invoke his intercession throughout the centuries, bent his neck under the sword, and went

00:08:05.420 --> 00:08:10.260
to carry off the trophies of eternal glory.

00:08:10.260 --> 00:08:16.340
Carrying out the saint's desire, his servant took his precious relics back to his country,

00:08:16.340 --> 00:08:23.720
to Lidda, the Ospolis, in Palestine, where innumerable miracles were worked in the great

00:08:23.720 --> 00:08:27.740
church that was built in his honor.

00:08:27.740 --> 00:08:33.860
The veneration of Saint George enjoyed enormous popularity throughout the Christian world, both

00:08:33.860 --> 00:08:36.260
East and West.

00:08:36.260 --> 00:08:42.020
He was chosen to be the protector of countries like Georgia and England.

00:08:42.020 --> 00:08:47.100
Thousands of churches have been dedicated to him, and every Christian soul sees him in

00:08:47.100 --> 00:08:54.900
the incarnation of the virtues of valor, patience in affliction, and trust in the help of grace

00:08:54.900 --> 00:09:02.100
that Christ, the leader in battle, has enjoined on all the soldiers enrolled in his army of

00:09:02.100 --> 00:09:04.340
devotion.

00:09:04.340 --> 00:09:11.580
Through the prayers of our Holy Father's, O Lord, Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us

00:09:11.580 --> 00:09:12.780
and save us.
